				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$L_{\mathrm{s}}$\end{document} ahead of adjustment of composition in northern summer, revealing that transport outpaces mixing (Trainer et al. 2019). The abundance of O2 does not vary in parallel with the other non-condensable gases. Its observed large range (1300 to 2200 ppmv), gradual increase in northern spring/summer, and interannual variability are not currently explained by known sources and sinks (Trainer et al. 2019).

